prompt: If region x is SW of region y and region y is E of region z, then which could be the possible relations between region x and region z?
answer:
The available information rules out every relation in which x is north of z, but leaves all southern or overlapping cases feasible. The relations that can be satisfied simultaneously with  

•  x SW y and  
•  y E z  

are:  

B, S, SW, SE, W, E
